### Login as Admin
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login as Regular User
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "user",
  "password": "user123"
}

### Example of unprotected resource access
GET http://localhost:8080/api/public/hello

### Example of protected resource access (using the JWT token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/secure/hello
Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}

### Using environment variables to store tokens
# @name loginAdmin
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("admin_token", response.body.token);
%}

### Using the saved admin token
GET http://localhost:8080/api/secure/hello
Authorization: Bearer {{admin_token}}